<subSubSection id="A90D04ADA3671D0CA4DAEFC76AA03093" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="50E060EA3164D3D18B7361A064BCBEB4" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F2DD9CB193116FB9300D96E656B7C8F" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
Persia, Prov. Azerbaijan occid.: In pratis paludosis SE Shahpur versus lacum Rezaiyeh (Urmia), 1300 m; 12 Jun 1971, 
<emphasis id="A22AB3BD88538AEECB29BA25CA3BD054" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Rechinger 41820</emphasis>
(holotype: W [W1972-0000975 image!; isotypes: B! [B 10_0272774], GZU [GZU000201751 image!], WU [WU0033125 image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A9E273361251CCF2D61E5D38FA3861E1" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C978F4B749F32AA2F89E50FE97FCC29B" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BDACC88F6EEA931E42A6AB3F79E821A1" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
The type collection of 
<taxonomicName id="7241FAF6FB03E6B4FA5A9C34945D6D7C" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa medica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medica">
<emphasis id="79AE36F7149E7DD23E89458A7158741B" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Eremopoa medica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly a perennial species of 
<taxonomicName id="D6D0EB413DCD1F699ABBB33208158350" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Puccinellia" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25F5E52D81E1F5DD6957F9CDFC64374D" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Puccinellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(possibly 
<taxonomicName id="108795AEB1BFC58E05AF401FE4AB108A" genus="P." lsidName="P. gigantea" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis id="CE709D6AF1BA360ECBF54A84BCBF205B" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Grossh.) Grossh.) with lemmas rounded on the back, a distinct short crown of callus hairs and papillae common on vegetative structures (pedicels and leaves). Material cited as 
<taxonomicName id="8F325EDA544629807623F70705A46A44" genus="E." lsidName="E. persica" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<taxonomicName id="9C45362112DDB7866CA1E55A7157713D" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. medica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="medica">
<emphasis id="9A2BD65DCCEEB8C5516DEC55C4810143" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">E. medica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="A23BFBDA790CECD068BD178634D7C825" author="Rahmanian, S" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Botany" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" pagination="8 - 15" refId="B43" refString="Rahmanian, S, Saeidi, H, Assadi, M, Rahiminejad, MR, 2014. A taxonomic revision of the genus Eremopoa Roschv. (Poaceae, Poeae) in Iran. Iranian Journal of Botany 20 (1): 8 - 15" title="A taxonomic revision of the genus Eremopoa Roschv. (Poaceae, Poeae) in Iran." volume="20" year="2014">Rahmanian et al. (2014</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5) appears to us to be 
<taxonomicName id="DBC45CB0EAE9CC013A90ED1EFCCE12C6" authority="subsp. persica" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica" subspecies="persica">Poa persica subsp. persica</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
; their description and illustration indicate an annual habit, pubescent lemmas and panicles with 10 or more branches per whorl. The single specimen (TARI 35082) cited was included in our molecular analysis and formed a clade with other 
<taxonomicName id="F33C38F8E7E95F4A0CBC32ADA90EE110" genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="4BA545AC30B5F453C15D6A8ACCA95816" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accessions in all trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="453C7442FA7548E0D2A8CEB0A457873E" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="invalid names, not vouchered">
<paragraph id="03EE8D227F4111F66192BF4FA80334C2" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Invalid names, not vouchered</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D736D83DBFE25FCE4BF9D9C8C36B8C88" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis id="33582AC1A0575F9350F34F5101F47C99" bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName id="C491DEC2C85E3C12DC144CC4D6AFE5DC" authorityName="Royle" authorityYear="1840" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Festuca amherstiana" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amherstiana">
<emphasis id="BDB10734479AB9EA6EBFD845E4E6DF97" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Festuca amherstiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nees, Ill. Bot. Himal. Mts. 417. 1839, nom. nud., name in list, no voucher.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27A5C931522ABE1344A5356DAC8E0714" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis id="039987493A5E78F87B184BB52D083570" bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Notes.</emphasis>
Kew GrassBase (Clayton et al. 2002+) indicates it is equal to 
<taxonomicName id="7F0C37B63BF69AEFFE88568270F152A1" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. persica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="A1CBC2BFECAB7B148A3D48D138471F08" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">E. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen K00078950 (ex P) (image!), 
<emphasis id="9EB718C1AB057DC7BE6345F01AC10618" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Voyage V. Jacquemont aux Indes orient. no. 1902</emphasis>
, has this name on the label. The specimen is certainly 
<taxonomicName id="4C831A8EDF80A02C9B3D570258400E68" genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphora" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="diaphora">
<emphasis id="302B6493CC5C272BFFB96763EBF7ED72" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. diaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="9FB1285AD5A5028C06A4EA2A6FCB5469" genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="FD245CF18AB4B72B78918E6B75D7A6D1" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
